==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intervocalic
<hw>In`ter*vo*cal"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Phon.)</fld>
<def>Situated between vowels; immediately preceded and followed by vowel
sounds, <as>as, <it>p</it> in <it>occupy</it>, <it>d</it> in
<it>idea</it>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>intervolution</ent>⟦br⟧
